## Fallback Approaches (if LI.FI is unavailable)

| | CCTP (Circle) | Across Protocol |
|---|---|---|
| **Speed** | 15–20 minutes | 1–2 minutes |
| **Security** | Highest — Circle burns/mints natively | High — UMA oracle, audited |
| **Cost** | Gas only (~$0.02 total) | Gas + 0.1–0.2% bridge fee |
| **Slippage** | Zero | Zero (fixed relayer quote) |
| **Custody risk** | None | Relayer fronts funds (repaid later) |
| **Best for** | Production / real money | Hackathon demo / fast UX |

---

## Option A — CCTP (Cross-Chain Transfer Protocol) by Circle

### How it works
Circle operates a burn-and-mint model: USDC is **destroyed** on Base and **freshly minted** on Polygon. No bridge pool, no wrapped tokens, no custodian.

```
User's Base Wallet
       │
       ▼
1. burnUSDC on Base
   TokenMessenger.depositForBurn(amount, destinationDomain=7, recipient, burnToken)
       │
       ▼
2. Circle attestation service monitors the burn event
   Waits for ~12 block confirmations on Base (~24 seconds)
   Circle signs an attestation (proof the burn happened)
       │
       ▼
3. Poll Circle API until attestation ready
   GET https://iris-api.circle.com/attestations/{messageHash}
   Typically ready in 10–15 minutes
       │
       ▼
4. Mint USDC on Polygon
   MessageTransmitter.receiveMessage(message, attestation)
   → Fresh USDC appears in recipient wallet on Polygon
```

### Exact contracts

| Contract | Base | Polygon |
|---|---|---|
| TokenMessenger | `0x1682Ae6375C4E4A97e4B583BC394c861A46D8962` | `0x9daF8c91AABE-...` |
| MessageTransmitter | `0xAD09780d193884d503182aD4588450C416D6F9D4` | `0xF3be9355363857-...` |

> Always verify current addresses at: [developers.circle.com/stablecoins/docs/cctp-protocol-contract](https://developers.circle.com/stablecoins/docs/cctp-protocol-contract)

### SDK / Code

```python
# Python backend (services/backend) — using web3.py
from web3 import Web3

w3_base = Web3(Web3.HTTPProvider(os.getenv("BASE_RPC_URL")))
w3_polygon = Web3(Web3.HTTPProvider(os.getenv("POLYGON_RPC_URL")))

TOKEN_MESSENGER_BASE = "0x1682Ae6375C4E4A97e4B583BC394c861A46D8962"
POLYGON_DOMAIN = 7

def burn_usdc_on_base(user_wallet, amount_usdc, recipient_on_polygon):
    # Step 1: Approve TokenMessenger to spend USDC
    # Step 2: Call depositForBurn
    tx = token_messenger.functions.depositForBurn(
        amount_usdc,          # amount in USDC units (6 decimals)
        POLYGON_DOMAIN,       # destination: Polygon = 7
        recipient_on_polygon,
        USDC_BASE_ADDRESS
    ).build_transaction({...})
    # Sign with user's smart wallet (via ERC-4337)
    return signed_tx_hash

def poll_attestation(message_hash: str) -> str:
    import requests, time
    url = f"https://iris-api.circle.com/attestations/{message_hash}"
    while True:
        r = requests.get(url).json()
        if r.get("status") == "complete":
            return r["attestation"]
        time.sleep(15)

def mint_usdc_on_polygon(message: bytes, attestation: str):
    tx = message_transmitter_polygon.functions.receiveMessage(
        message, bytes.fromhex(attestation[2:])
    ).build_transaction({...})
    return signed_tx_hash
```

### Gas breakdown (CCTP)
| Step | Chain | Estimated cost |
|---|---|---|
| Approve USDC | Base | ~$0.001 |
| depositForBurn | Base | ~$0.01 |
| receiveMessage (mint) | Polygon | ~$0.005 |
| **Total** | | **~$0.016** |

