## Recommended Stack (Hackathon)

| Layer | Technology | Why |
|---|---|---|
| User wallet on Base | **Coinbase Smart Wallet** (ERC-4337) | Native Base support, MPC key management, free on testnet |
| Bridge aggregator | **LI.FI SDK** (`@lifi/sdk`) | Single integration, auto-picks best route, USDC native output |
| Bridge fallback | **Across Protocol** | LI.FI's most common pick anyway |
| Gas sponsorship | **Coinbase Paymaster** | Free on Base Sepolia testnet |
| Polygon RPC | **Alchemy / QuickNode** | Reliable, free tier for hackathon |
| Base RPC | **Base Sepolia RPC** (`https://sepolia.base.org`) | Official, free |
| USDC faucet (testnet) | **Circle testnet faucet** | Free testnet USDC on Base Sepolia |

---

## End-to-End Flow in Your App

```
1. User loads wallet via MPesa
   → Transak/MoonPay: KES → USDC → deposited to user's Base smart wallet

2. User pays for premium advice (stays on Base)
   → x402: $0.10 USDC from user's Base wallet → NORT's Base wallet
   → Instant, no bridge needed

3. User triggers trade (auto or manual)
   → AutoTradeEngine calls bridge service

4. Bridge service (your backend):
   a. Call LI.FI REST API → get best route for USDC Base→Polygon
   b. Show user: "Bridge $50 USDC via Across (fee: $0.08, arrives in ~2 min)"
   c. User confirms (or auto-confirm if auto_trade_enabled)
   d. Sign and execute from user's Base smart wallet

5. ~2 minutes later: USDC on Polygon
   → Backend detects arrival (listen to Polygon transfer event)
   → Execute Polymarket CLOB signed order
   → On-chain tx hash returned as receipt

6. Bot notifies user:
   "✅ Bridge complete — $49.92 USDC on Polygon. Trade executing..."
   "✅ Trade logged: YES on market-001 at 72% odds. Tx: 0xabc..."
```

